576	session-1776284126108	ASSISTANT	The formula to calculate the risk score in the AI-Driven Fraud Detection System is as follows:\n\n**Fraud Score = 1 - ?(1 - RuleScore)**\n\nHere, each rule contributes a risk signal (0 to 1) based on its output. The final fraud score is calculated by applying the formula above to the risk signals from each rule. The score range and corresponding decisions are as follows:\n\n- **0.00 to 0.49**: VALID - Safe transaction\n- **0.50 to 0.84**: ALERT - Suspicious, needs monitoring\n- **0.85 to 1.00**: FRAUD - High-risk, should be blocked\n\nThis formula is used to combine the risk signals from multiple rules to determine the overall fraud risk of a transaction.	2026-04-16 11:49:26.796894	adminuser7
